STATE OF OREGON, Respondent, v. CHARLES EDWARD PASCHAL (No. C 72-05-1477 Cr), Appellant. 507 P2d 1157 Gary D. Babcoclc, Public Defender, Salem, argued the cause and filed the brief for appellant. John W. Osburn, Solicitor General, Salem, argued the cause for respondent. With him on the brief was Lee Johnson, Attorney General, Salem.

Argued March 29,

affirmed March 29, 1973

Before Schwab, Chief Judge, and Fort and Thornton, Judges.
